{
  "texts": [
    "The VADLP model [33] constructed multilayer graphs to integrate multiple similarities and employed variance autoencoders and CNN for lncRNAdisease interaction inference.",
    "The gGATLDA model [34] utilized attention mechanisms at the graph level.",
    "During the graph construction process, each disease-lncRNA pair is extracted to form a subgraph for lncRNA-disease relationship calculation.",
    "The MLMKDNN model [35] proposed a deep multi-kernel learning method, which included feature matrix construction, kernel space mapping, and deep neural network fusion.",
    "The kernel space mapping technique was applied to transform the feature matrix, enabling effective integration using deep neural networks for fusion."
  ]
}